1. Albert Einstein - the renowned physicist who revolutionized our understanding of the universe;
2. Marie Curie - pioneering scientist known for her work on radioactivity;
3. Pablo Picasso - the iconic artist who redefined visual art with his innovative techniques;
4. Mahatma Gandhi - the influential political and spiritual leader whose methods of non-violent civil disobedience changed the world.

As we sit down for dinner, I would listen intently as each shares their experiences, insights, and contributions to the realms of science, art, and politics. The conversation would undoubtedly be rich and stimulating, providing profound insights into the human condition, the challenges of innovation, and the impact of one's efforts to shape the world.
